headline.print_headline: Algeria Soccer Death Seen as Part of Wider Ills
headline.main: Algeria Soccer Death Seen as Part of Wider Ills

lead_paragraph: The rocks came raining down after the final whistle of the Algerian soccer match, an increasingly common ritual in stadiums across the country. This time, the violence ended in tragedy: Hit in the head, Albert Ebosse, the league's top goal scorer last season, crumbled to the ground and died in a hospital.
